# Paper and Claim Discipline

Apply when editing paper drafts, docs, benchmark definitions, and claim-bearing source comments/text.

## Synchronization Rules
- Paper and implementation must stay synchronized.
- Benchmark definitions, labels, schemas, baselines, and metrics in writing must match actual artifacts.

## Claim Boundaries
- Do not claim broad clinical reasoning ability.
- Do not claim deployment readiness.
- Do not imply physician-level equivalence.
- Prefer workflow-level claims about evidence retrieval, abstention, action grounding, and structured execution.

## Change Trigger
- If benchmark semantics change, update paper placeholders and relevant docs in the same workstream.
